Checking and processing of enum is a really frequent case in our library, maybe it make sense to move processing of enums to `BaseProvider` and it this case we can use this:

```python
def hashtags(self, quantity, category):
    param = self.validate_enum(category, Hashtag)
    hashtags = HASHTAGS[param.value]

    if int(quantity) == 1:
        return self.random.choice(hashtags)

    tags = [self.random.choice(hashtags) for _ in range(int(quantity))]
    return tags
```

instead this:
```python
def hashtags(self, quantity: int = 4,
             category: Hashtag = None) -> Union[str, list]:
    if category is None:
        category = Hashtag.get_random_item()

    if category and category in Hashtag:
        hashtags = HASHTAGS[category.value]
    else:
        raise NonEnumerableError(Hashtag)

    if int(quantity) == 1:
        return self.random.choice(hashtags)

    tags = [self.random.choice(hashtags) for _ in range(int(quantity))]
    return tags
```

