Say we want to pass a list of subnets to a Fargate definition, currently we have to do
```hcl
output "subnet_1" {...}
output "subnet_2" {...}
output "subnet_3" {...}
```

```yml
services:
 - name: example
    vpc_configuration:
        subnets:
            ${terraform.subnet_1}
            ${terraform.subnet_2}
            ${terraform.subnet_3}
```

This means that you have to list them out. Can you do something like:

```hcl
output "app_subnet_ids" {
    value = ["list of subnet ids", ...]
}
```

```yml
services:
 - name: example
    vpc_configuration:
        subnets: ${terraform.app_subnet_ids}
```

And if not, would you consider this as a feature? Being able to pass lists directly from terraform outputs would make certain things really flexible.

